{
  "category": "enhancement",
  "description": "Identify all instances of expensive in-render computations — such as filtering transcription segments, computing word counts, or building display strings from raw data — and wrap them in useMemo with precise dependency arrays. Co-locate a performance budget comment (e.g., '< 2ms') to flag future regressions.\n\n**Rationale:** Derived data re-computed on every render is a silent performance drain. In transcription-heavy views where state updates are frequent, memoizing expensive derivations can reduce render time by 40–70% for those specific computations.",
  "title": "useMemo for Derived State in Transcription Components",
